LLM: Google Gemini, Nano Babana 2
Date: 2026-03-01

Draw infographic, to highlight speed reading idead: the "Saccade"—the
technical term for the jerky movement the eye makes between fixation
points.

For the Long Lines: Use a zigzagging red arrow to show the tiring
distance the eye travels.

For the Short Lines: Use a straight, vertical arrow to show how the
eye simply "glides" down the center.
